[2026-03-17T15:35:07Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K3Pcjxnz2xdtCmn1qeg5u4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a comprehensive summary document based on my exploration:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: `internal/evolution/` Package\n\n### 1. Files in internal/evolution/\n\nThe package contains 21 Go files (20 source, 1 configuration):\n\n**Core Types & Configuration:**\n- `types.go` - Main domain types for evolution system\n- `fitness.go` - Fitness evaluation and Pareto front computation\n- `population.go` - Population management for candidate variants\n- `selector.go` - Candidate selection strategies\n\n**Evolution Pipeline Components:**\n- `collector.go` - Gathers data needed for evolution analysis\n- `classifier.go` - Categorizes runs (bug, feedback, feature, enhancement, chore)\n- `reflector.go` - Examines execution traces and extracts lessons\n- `curator.go` - Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE principles\n- `scriptgen.go` - LLM-based script generation for new steps\n- `orchestrator.go` - Wires all evolution stages together\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `audit.go` - Records evolution actions and manages snapshots\n- `trigger.go` - Debounces evolution pipeline runs per project+workflow\n- `llmclient.go` - LLM client interface\n\n**Test Files:**\n- `types_test.go`, `fitness_test.go`, `population_test.go`, `selector_test.go`\n- `trigger_test.go`, `scriptgen_test.go`, `evolution_test.go`, `corruption_test.go`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Core Types Defined in the Package\n\n#### **Candidate & Fitness Types**\n\nFrom `types.go`:\n- `Candidate` - Prompt variant in GEPA population with ID, PromptID, Content, Generation, ParentID, and FitnessScores\n- `FitnessScores` - Multi-objective fitness with Scores map, Total, Count, and Average\n- `RunScoreRecord` - Simple score outcome: CandidateID, RunID, Score, Details\n- `PopulationConfig` - Configuration for GEPA-style population evolution with Enabled, MaxCandidates, MinRunsToPromote\n\nFrom `fitness.go`:\n- `FitnessRecord` - Metrics from run evaluation: RunID, WorkflowName, Candidate, Success, RetryCount, Duration, Timestamp\n- `CandidateFitness` - Aggregated fitness across runs: Candidate, SuccessRate, Efficiency, RunCount\n- **Pareto Front Functions:**\n  - `Dominates(a, b CandidateFitness) bool` - Returns true if a dominates b in multi-objective comparison\n  - `ComputeParetoFront(candidates []CandidateFitness) []CandidateFitness` - Returns non-dominated set\n\n#### **Population Management Types**\n\nFrom `population.go`:\n- `Population` - Manages candidate prompt variants per step with ProjectDir and StepName\n- `CandidateMeta` - JSONL entry with ID, Status (active/archived/promoted), CreatedAt, ParentID, Score\n- `Assignment` - Maps workflow run to candidate used with RunID, CandidateID, AssignedAt\n\nDisk layout:\n```\n.cloche/evolution/population/<step-name>/\n  candidate-001.md\n  candidate-002.md\n  meta.jsonl\n  assignments.jsonl\n```\n\n#### **Evolution Pipeline Types**\n\nFrom `types.go`:\n- `CollectedData` - Input to Classifier and Reflector with Runs, Captures, KnowledgeBase, CurrentPrompts, CurrentWorkflow, etc.\n- `Lesson` - Structured insight with ID, Category (prompt_improvement/new_step), StepType, Target, Insight, SuggestedAction, Evidence[], Confidence\n- `EvolutionResult` - Records evolution pass output with ID, ProjectDir, WorkflowName, TriggerRunID, Timestamp, Classification, Changes[], KnowledgeDelta\n- `Change` - Single file modification with Type, File, Reason, Snapshot\n\n#### **Other Key Types**\n\n- `Classifier` - Has LLM interface\n- `Reflector` - Has LLM and MinConfidence fields\n- `Curator` - Has LLM and AuditLogger for ACE-style curation\n- `ScriptGenerator` - LLM-based script generation\n- `Orchestrator` - Wires all stages together\n- `LLMClient` interface - `Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Test Patterns\n\n**Test Helper Pattern:**\n```go\nfunc newTestPopulation(t *testing.T) *Population {\n    t.Helper()\n    return &Population{\n        ProjectDir: t.TempDir(),\n        StepName:   \"code\",\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Table-Driven Tests:**\n- Used extensively in `fitness_test.go`, `selector_test.go`\n- Consistent structure with `name`, input fields, expected fields\n- Tests organized in `for _, tt := range tests { t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) { ... }) }`\n\n**Test Organization:**\n- Test files use `package evolution` (not `evolution_test` subpackage), except `fitness_test.go` uses `package evolution_test`\n- Uses `testify/require` and `testify/assert` for assertions\n- `t.TempDir()` for filesystem operations\n\n**Common Test Patterns:**\n- JSON marshaling/unmarshaling tests\n- Disk layout verification\n- Error case handling (NotFound, Invalid, etc.)\n- Behavior verification (e.g., distribution tests for selection strategies)\n\n**Notable Test Files:**\n- `fitness_test.go` - Tests Pareto front computation with complex multi-objective scenarios\n- `population_test.go` - Tests JSONL read/write, file layout, promotion workflow\n- `selector_test.go` - Tests 70/30 split distribution (1000+ iteration sampling)\n- `evolution_test.go` (40KB) - Large integration test with fakeLLM stub\n\n---\n\n### 4. Go Conventions Used in This Project\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)` for error wrapping (Go 1.13+)\n- Functions return `(T, error)` tuple\n- Error wrapping with format verbs for context propagation\n- Example: `return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"reading target prompt %s: %w\", lesson.Target, err)`\n\n**Naming Conventions:**\n- Receiver methods: `(c *Curator)`, `(p *Population)`, `(o *Orchestrator)`\n- Interface names: `LLMClient`, `Classifier`, `Reflector` (noun-like)\n- Unexported helpers: `lessonAlreadyPresent`, `promptSanityCheck`, `stripCodeFences`\n- Constants for status: `candidateStatusActive`, `candidateStatusArchived`, `candidateStatusPromoted`\n\n**File Organization:**\n- One main struct/concept per file (e.g., `population.go`, `fitness.go`, `curator.go`)\n- Type definitions at the top of files\n- Helper/internal functions after main implementations\n- Tests in adjacent `*_test.go` files\n\n**Context Usage:**\n- `ctx context.Context` as first parameter in async/blocking operations\n- Example: `Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)`\n\n**JSON Handling:**\n- `json:\"field_name\"` tags with `omitempty` for optional fields\n- Examples:\n  - `ParentID string `json:\"parent_id,omitempty\"`\n  - `Details string `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n- Manual JSONL parsing: line-by-line unmarshaling with error skipping\n\n**File Operations:**\n- Use absolute paths internally\n- `filepath.Join()` for path construction\n- `os.MkdirAll(dir, 0755)` before file writes\n- `os.O_APPEND|os.O_CREATE|os.O_WRONLY` for JSONL appends\n\n**Concurrent Data Structures:**\n- `sync.Mutex` with `defer Unlock()` pattern\n- Example in `trigger.go`: protecting `timers map[string]*time.Timer`\n\n**Testing:**\n- Early exit helpers: `t.Helper()` marks helper functions\n- Assertions use `assert` (non-fatal) and `require` (fatal) from testify\n- Subtests with `t.Run(name, func(t *testing.T) {...})`\n\n**Domain-Driven Design:**\n- Clear separation: `internal/domain/` for business types (Run, StepExecution)\n- `internal/evolution/` for evolution-specific logic\n- `internal/ports/` for interfaces (adapters pattern)\n- Hexagonal architecture: domain logic independent of infrastructure\n\n**String Processing:**\n- `strings.TrimSpace()`, `strings.Contains()`, `strings.Split()` for parsing\n- Regex via `regexp.MustCompile()` for complex patterns\n- Case-insensitive matching with `strings.ToLower()`\n\n**Time Handling:**\n- `time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)` for ISO timestamps\n- `time.Duration` for measurements\n- `time.After`, `time.AfterFunc` for debouncing\n\n**Type Comments:**\n- Brief comments above exported types and functions\n- Example: `// Candidate represents a prompt variant in a GEPA population...`\n- Structured comments explain parameters and behavior\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Patterns and Design Principles\n\n**Evolution Pipeline Flow:**\n1. Collect → Classify → Reflect → Execute (Curate or AddStep) → Audit\n\n**Multi-Objective Optimization:**\n- Uses Pareto dominance for fitness comparison\n- Two objectives: SuccessRate and Efficiency (inverse of duration + retries)\n- `ComputeParetoFront()` identifies non-dominated candidates\n\n**Population-Based Prompt Evolution (GEPA):**\n- Maintains candidate pool for each workflow step\n- JSONL-based metadata tracking (meta.jsonl, assignments.jsonl)\n- Promotion workflow: snapshot current base → promote winner → archive others\n\n**Candidate Selection:**\n- 70% Pareto front (exploitation) + 30% non-front (exploration)\n- Handles edge cases: empty pools, missing data\n\n**Error Recovery & Corruption Safeguards:**\n- Sanity checks on LLM output (conversational detection, structure validation)\n- Fallback: direct append if LLM returns meta-conversation\n- Code fence stripping for safety\n\n**Knowledge Base Management:**\n- JSONL format with lesson IDs to prevent re-applying lessons\n- Deduplication against knowledge base before execution\n\n---\n\n### 6. Summary of File Locations\n\n| Type | File Path |\n|------|-----------|\n| Candidate & Fitness | `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go`, `fitness.go` |\n| Population Management | `/workspace/internal/evolution/population.go` |\n| Pareto Front Functions | `/workspace/internal/evolution/fitness.go` |\n| Evolution Pipeline | `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` |\n| Lesson Extraction | `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go` |\n| Prompt Curation | `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` |\n| Script Generation | `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go` |\n| Run Classification | `/workspace/internal/evolution/classifier.go` |\n| Data Collection | `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go` |\n| Audit Logging | `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` |\n| Selection Strategy | `/workspace/internal/evolution/selector.go` |\n| Trigger/Debouncing | `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go` |\n| Tests | `/workspace/internal/evolution/*_test.go` |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Related Domain Types\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`:\n- `Run` - Workflow execution record with ID, WorkflowName, State (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled), StepExecutions, timing info\n- `StepExecution` - Individual step result with StepName, Result, StartedAt, CompletedAt, Logs, GitRef\n- `RunState` - String type for terminal states\n\nThese are imported and used extensively in fitness evaluation and data collection."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a469350f86fdf2137 (use SendMessage with to: 'a469350f86fdf2137' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57667\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 52599</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a76bb48f-05af-4174-aa66-b2697e9be94c","uuid":"b805bd85-a4ff-483c-968d-76b2eef4e57b","timestamp":"2026-03-17T15:33:50.218Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the internal/evolution/ directory and any related domain types. I need to understand:\n1. What files already exist in internal/evolution/\n2. What types are defined there (especially Candidate, fitness-related types, Pareto front types)\n3. Any existing test patterns in the evolution package\n4. General Go conventions used in this project (error handling, naming, etc.)\n\nSearch thoroughly - check internal/evolution/*.go, internal/domain/ for related types, and any existing test files.","agentId":"a469350f86fdf2137","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a comprehensive summary document based on my exploration:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: `internal/evolution/` Package\n\n### 1. Files in internal/evolution/\n\nThe package contains 21 Go files (20 source, 1 configuration):\n\n**Core T