[2026-03-17T15:36:12Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JCNU6ufbr5eM9KvV5AFZjb","type":"tool_result","content":"   484→### Pareto Front\n   485→\n   486→`ComputeParetoFront` returns the non-dominated set using standard Pareto\n   487→dominance: candidate A dominates B when A is at least as good in all objectives\n   488→and strictly better in at least one. The front represents the optimal tradeoff\n   489→between reliability and speed — no candidate on the front can be improved in one\n   490→objective without sacrificing the other.\n   491→\n   492→### Population Configuration\n   493→\n   494→Population-based evolution is controlled by `PopulationConfig`:\n   495→\n   496→```go\n   497→type PopulationConfig struct {\n   498→    Enabled          bool\n   499→    MaxCandidates    int\n   500→    MinRunsToPromote int\n   501→}\n   502→```\n   503→\n   504→## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n   505→\n   506→- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n   507→  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n   508→- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n   509→- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n   510→  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n   511→- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n   512→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70e783a4-e8f4-4ca0-9162-12684b626521","uuid":"402a3f74-5c63-413e-8387-abcb59550fff","timestamp":"2026-03-17T15:35:56.669Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"### Pareto Front\n\n`ComputeParetoFront` returns the non-dominated set using standard Pareto\ndominance: candidate A dominates B when A is at least as good in all objectives\nand strictly better in at least one. The front represents the optimal tradeoff\nbetween reliability and speed — no candidate on the front can be improved in one\nobjective without sacrificing the other.\n\n### Population Configuration\n\nPopulation-based evolution is controlled by `PopulationConfig`:\n\n```go\ntype PopulationConfig struct {\n    Enabled          bool\n    MaxCandidates    int\n    MinRunsToPromote int\n}\n```\n\n## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n\n- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n","numLines":29,"startLine":484,"totalLines":512}}}
